article.headline: Hicks, Norfolk State fall short against Hampton
article.linkText: Hampton survives frantic late rally by Norfolk State
article.story:
Quarterfinal Results
Florida A&M 55, Coppin State 53
RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Devin Green scored 18 of his 22 points in the second half and Hampton survived a huge second half by Chakowby Hicks on Thursday to beat Norfolk State 64-62 in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference tournament quarterfinals. The defending tournament champion Pirates (18-10) led most of the second half, but never pulled away and withstood two 3-pointers by Hicks in the final 19 seconds. A third 3-point try by Hicks missed just before the final buzzer sounded. Norfolk State (14-15), which beat the Pirates 48-44 on Saturday, got 24 points from Hicks and 19 from Daryl Towe, who had 15 of those after the intermission. Barry Hairston added 16 for Hampton, which led 27-18 at halftime, then had its lead wiped out by the Spartans' 12-0 run. Towe scored seven points in the burst, Hicks five. Two ties followed before a 7-0 run by Hampton gave the Pirates the lead for good. Hicks' 3-pointer with 19 seconds to play pulled the Spartans within 61-59. After Mackel Purvis made two free throws for the Pirates with 11 seconds left, Hicks connected again with six seconds to play, pulling the Spartans to 63-62. Green made a free throw with five seconds to play, but missed the second one and Hicks' attempt at a game-winner 3-pointer missed as time expired. The third-seeded Pirates will play Florida A&M, which defeated Coppin State 55-53 in another MEAC quarterfinal, on Friday.
